LAGOS – President of the West Africa Boxing Union (WABU), Remi Aboderin, has lauded Nigerian boxer, Taye Olowu and his opponent from Ghana Justice Addy that battled for the West African Boxing Union welterweight title at boxing show recently organized in Lagos by Saleh Gloves Promotions. Although Nigeria’s Taiwo ‘Gentle Boy’ Olowu secured a round three knockout in the action packed bout, the Ghanaian, Justice Addy still got a commendation from the WABU President who sanctioned and supervised the bout for a brilliant performance. Aboderin, who is also the Secretary-General of the Nigerian Boxing Board of Control (NBB of C), also thumped up Saleh Fawaz, the promoter of the first boxing show to be held at the beach, Moist Beach, Oniru Private Beach, Lagos for a well organized show.